<br>
You should have to take a rigorous drivers test to get your license, and retake the full test every 5 years, until age or medical condition requires more frequent testing.  Fewer people on the roads, who are all decent drivers means we can raise speed limits, improve traffic flow, and basically stop catering to the lowest common denominator.<br>
<br>
People have forgotten that driving is a privalege and not a right.  DWI - one strike and you lose your license for life.  i make small considerations for fender benders and speeding cause face it, all of us have days when we make a stupid mistake.  but major screw-ups, drunk driving, excessive speeding - you should be taken off the road for good.<br>
<br>
I lost the same friend herne did - got hit at a red light while he was sitting on his motorcycle.  driver of the pickup was going 40, never saw him sitting there, not to mention the red light.<br>
<br>
Baekin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umielked.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mielked</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/19/02 6:39:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> Just a quick question for those that think that the One Time Offender should suffer a life time.<br>
<br>
Do you believe in the death penalty?<br>
<br>
Can a criminal be rehabbed?<br>
<br>
When you talk about DWI you talk about alcohol, but DWI includes any impairment to include other drugs which marijuana is a part of?<br>
<br>
I agree DWI is something that needs to be dealt with in a more sever way, but to sentence a life punishment on every case?  This leads to corruption and wrongful interpretation..  <br>
<br>
I don't believe in the death penalty, and i think with time everyone can learn to be a productive citizen.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion.  SSneak  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxunathewizardess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xuna the Wizardess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/20/02 1:35:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> Actually DUI is driving under any influence which impairs your driving.  Drugs or Achocol are the most common influences.  But my aunt was actually given a DUI aka Driving Under the Influence because she was sleepy.  Drunk driving laws should be more harsh but why even give people the chance to get the one strike and therefore making them a relatively useless member of society.  Lets face it in most places if you don't have a car you don't have work.  I don't want Jim Bean living off of me and the welfare system because he can't get a job at 31 years old because he was drunk driving at 22.  People can recover people can change. <br>
<br>
If you really want change do this.<br>
1. If you get a DWI or DUI and nothing happened ie. no damage was done to people of property.  Keep the punishment the same as it is now.<br>
<br>
2. If you get a DWI/DUI and you damaged any property then enforce a stricter version of the penality.  Like 2 years suspended plus a hefty fine.<br>
<br>
3. If you get a DWI/DUI and you injure another person.  Then this person should lose thier ability to drive for a period ranging from 5-15 years and they should also be tried as if they had committed assault with a deadly weapon.<br>
<br>
4. If you get a DWI/DUI and you kill someone.  Then this person should never sit behind a wheel of a car again and should also be tried as if they had committed Murder.<br>
<br>
But if you really want to try your best to stop this install breath starters in all cars to where the driver would have to &quot;blow&quot; start the car.  Sure this won't stop Bill Whitenose, the coke addict, from driving but Jim Bean won't be driving home.<br>
<br>
Have car insurance companies pick up the tabs on thier insured when they choice to take a cab home.  (These companies could raise the rates of those that more frequently use this service but hell they rip us off everyday anyways).<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents worth.<br>
<br>
